==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polyneme
<hw>Pol"y*neme</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> +
Gr. <?/ thread.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous
species of tropical food fishes of the family <fam>Polynemid⟦ae⟧</fam>.
They have several slender filaments, often very long, below the pectoral
fin. Some of them yield isinglass of good quality. Called also
<altname>threadfish</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polynemoid</ent>⟦br⟧
